cs0x65.parkinglot.command

Interface Parser<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the domain specific target class that backs the Command(s) generated by the parser on successful parsing.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultParserImpl

    public interface Parser<T>
    Interface for parsing the command text. The implementation class is expected to provide below functionality - :
    • Syntactic validations: to make sure the command supplied is amongst the set of supported commands and & adheres to the grammar/syntax of the command.
    • Building domain specific Command instances that are backed by the domain implementation class and where T is the actual target to carry out the supplied command. Effectively, Parser also forms the bridge between the textual commands supplied and the supporting domain classes by building instances of the Command<T>. It is responsibility of the parser implementation to make sure all the necessary information and metadata is supplied to the Command<T> instances for their correct execution. Refer DefaultParserImpl which is the domain specific implementation of the Parser pertaining to ParkingLot.
